01.10 COMMENT NINE VALUE DESCRIPTIVE STATISTICS
01.20 COMMENT ENTER EACH OBSERVATION WHEN ASKED
01.30 SET S=0
01.40 SET Q=0
01.50 ASK A
01.60 SET S=S+A
01.70 SET Q=Q+A^2
01.80 ASK B
01.90 SET S=S+B
02.10 SET Q=Q+B^2
02.20 ASK C
02.30 SET S=S+C
02.40 SET Q=Q+C^2
02.50 ASK D
02.60 SET S=S+D
02.70 SET Q=Q+D^2
02.80 ASK E
02.90 SET S=S+E
03.10 SET Q=Q+E^2
03.20 ASK F
03.30 SET S=S+F
03.40 SET Q=Q+F^2
03.50 ASK G
03.60 SET S=S+G
03.70 SET Q=Q+G^2
03.80 ASK H
03.90 SET S=S+H
04.10 SET Q=Q+H^2
04.20 ASK I
04.30 SET S=S+I
04.40 SET Q=Q+I^2
04.50 SET M=S/9
04.60 SET V=(Q-S^2/9)/8
04.70 SET D=SQRT(V)
04.80 COMMENT PRINT SUM MEAN VARIANCE DEVIATION
04.90 PRINT S,!,M,!,V,!,D
05.10 COMMENT THIS IS SAMPLE VARIANCE USING N MINUS ONE
05.20 COMMENT THE ONE PASS FORMULA SAVES ALL INPUT VALUES
05.30 COMMENT LARGE CLOSE VALUES CAN LOSE SOME PRECISION
05.40 COMMENT CONSTANT INPUT SHOULD GIVE ZERO DEVIATION
05.50 COMMENT INPUT ORDER DOES NOT CHANGE THE FORMULAS
05.60 COMMENT SUM AND SQUARE SUM REMAIN AVAILABLE AS S Q
05.70 COMMENT RESULTS USE THE ACTIVE MK61 NUMBER FORMAT
05.80 EXIT
